A warder attached to Kangeta GK Prison in Meru County has been arrested over claims he was planning to kill his girlfriend.   The suspect is said to have confided in his colleagues that he planned to kill the woman, a student at Mt Kenya University, for defrauding him Sh900,000.   The suspect, who has since been transferred to Igembe, was arrested in a house at Kisii Estate in Thika, Kiambu County, on Friday.  A detective, who did not wish to be named, said the suspect's colleagues alerted the police as soon as he told them of his plan. They also informed the woman of what her boyfriend was planning so she could take caution.  Suspects in Kianjokoma brothers’ murders want bodies exhumed  Suspected serial killer Evans Wanjala charged with the murder of three girls  Four night guards murdered in cold blood in Siaya  Man arrested for allegedly hacking disabled son to death "It was reported that the officer was seen with a gun in a sack at Kangeta Police Station. We quickly alerted detectives who swung into action to save the woman's life," said one of the suspect's colleagues.  The suspect recorded a statement at Thika Police Station.   Murder Mystery: FBI joins investigations into the disappearance & murder of Bashir Mohammed  Police detain a couple and their son for allegedly beating their 15-year-old daughter to death  The widow of Jacob Juma has accused police of dragging their feet in the hunt for Juma’s killers By Muriithi Mugo | 1 day ago By Muriithi Mugo | 4 days ago By Jane Mugambi | 5 days ago By Muriithi Mugo | 5 days ago The grey areas in President Uhuru Kenyatta’s quest for a successor to secure his legacy